race.comment: YELLOWJACKET (12) has savaged the line in her two runs over the border and looks ready to peak. Will likely get back from the wide draw and be saved for one last crack at them. Leading player. CATHAY EXPRESS (7) debuts for the Bain & Taylor yard as an Alabama Express filly out of Cathay. Has a Morphettville jumpout placing to her name and looks set for a bright start. KOCIAN (10) is a King's Legacy filly out of Majestic Faith making her debut. Trial winner last time and fitter for the experience. No shock if she fires first-up. ORLOVA (11) resumes for the Clarken & Macgillivray team and has clearly come on during the break, winning a Murray Bridge trial. Can play a major role fresh. DIRTY OLD TOWN (8) is knocking on the door after two consecutive placings. Peaking now and firmly among the chances.
